--Clear the confusion between GROUP BY and ORDER BY 

ORDER BY
You have loose marbles on the floor, you place them in line. You have red, green, and yellow 100 altogether in a line
GROUP BY 
You have the marbles, you put them in a bucket by colour, 60 red in one bucket, 20 yellow in another bucket, and 
	The remaining 20 yellow in another bucket.
====================================================================================================================

The order of clauses in SQL
SELECT
DISTINCT
TOP
WHERE
GROUP BY
HAVING
ORDER BY = expensive operation as it goes through the entire database 

Worst combo using group by and order by, limit rows when querying if possible. Sorting is expensive

Use WINDOW FUNCTION INSTEAD. It is more flexible too.

